Ivan Popov <pin@math.chalmers.se> wrote:
> Just wondering if there is any technical reason for
> scsi disk driver not being able to spin disks down on idle timeout,
> like ide does.
There used to be support for this, look for the scsi-idle patch to
sd.c. You maybe want to backup your data first and apply it by hand.
